&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Schools ICT Engineer&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Location: &lt;/strong&gt;St Helens, UK&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Work mode:&lt;/strong&gt; Onsite 5 days a week&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT US&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Agilisys is at the forefront of digital transformation and innovation in the public services sector. With over two decades of experience, we have established ourselves as a trusted partner for governments, local authorities, and organisations nationwide. Our mission is to empower our clients to deliver exceptional public services by harnessing the full potential of technology and data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;OUR VALUES&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partnership: We become one team with our clients, helping them navigate change and stay agile.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Integrity: We care deeply, going beyond the brief to make meaningful change happen.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Innovation: We bring together the right technologies and expertise to design solutions that work.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Passion: We are dedicated to improving public services and, ultimately, people&#39;s lives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;THE ROLE&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Key Responsibilities&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Schools ICT Engineer is a vital role within Agilisys, providing high‑quality, onsite ICT support within a large secondary school in St Helens. You will play a key part in ensuring the smooth operation of day‑to‑day school IT services, supporting staff, students, and visitors, and maintaining a reliable, high‑availability environment.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Specific Duties&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide face‑to‑face and remote support to students, staff, and visitors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Log, manage, and resolve ICT incidents within defined SLAs and KPIs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver exceptional customer service at all times&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build, configure, and deploy end‑user devices for staff and students&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Install and update applications on user devices&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support printers, projectors, and other school equipment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete administrative tasks including asset management and documentation&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support school events such as open evenings, parents&#39; evenings, and other scheduled activities&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Work collaboratively with other ICT engineers to maintain a reliable, high‑availability environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Typical working hours are 8:00am – 4:00pm, Monday to Friday, with flexibility required based on school and business needs.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Opportunity&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This role is an excellent opportunity to build hands‑on experience within an education environment, working closely with end users and technical teams. You will gain exposure to a wide range of technologies while directly supporting teaching and learning through high‑quality ICT services.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;ABOUT YOU&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ideal candidate will be driven, customer‑focused, and enthusiastic about delivering high‑quality ICT support within an educational environment, with a strong track record of problem‑solving and delivering results.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;The Ideal Candidate&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong knowledge of Microsoft operating systems and products (Windows 10/11 and Windows Server)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience supporting hardware and software, including PCs, laptops, printers, and projectors&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of networking fundamentals and troubleshooting in a managed environment&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Familiarity with mixed Apple and Microsoft environments, including basic Apple device support&lt;/li&gt

